1. c4 {The somewhat non-forcing nature of playing c4 on the first move means that Black has a bit more freedom to play something offbeat than he would against e4 or d4. Moves like 1... b6 become sort of reasonable, and we should make sure to cover the sidelines properly. Still, I don't find them too challenging, and I think we can knock them all out in one section.} 
1. d5 {This is extremely stupid, and basically, you can only expect it as a premove when playing online and someone expects 1. d4.•1...d62.g3As usual, we follow up with 2. g3. This line should not have any independent value for Black, as I cannot imagine him avoiding e7-e5, g7-g6, or c7-c5.2...e53.Bg2This will be covered in the 1... e5 course.•1...d62.g3Nf63.Bg2c64.Nc3This will transpose to the g6/ Bg7 sections of the course.•1...d62.g3c53.Bg2This will be covered in the 1... c5 course.} 
