5. Nf6
6. Nc3
6. Bc5
7. e3
7. O-O
8. Be2
8. Qe7
9. O-O
9. Rd8 {This would be consistent with the general Smith-Morra plan, but the tempo up for us means Black's play it entirely toothless.} 
10. Qc2 {Since Black's bishop is not yet on f5, we need not fear the knight coming to b4.} 
10. Bf5
11. Ne4 {Black is more or less just a pawn down.} 
