15. Be3
15. O-O
16. Rac1
16. Qxe5 {It's quite nice that this does not work so well. Still, it is a natural move that White should be ready for, since precision is required.} 
17. Bf4
17. Qf6
18. Rc7 {White's pieces are springing to life. It is a very bad sign for Black that the machine wants him to play Bb7-c8. This line is analyzed in greater detail here.} 
