6. d3 {As usual, I want to put the pawn on d3 rather than d4 against the bishop on f5. This not only restricts the bishop, but also allows White to go Bc1-e3 and attack the queen, forcing Black to release the tension when normally he would prefer to just leave the queens staring at each other.} 
6. e6 {I really struggle to imagine an intelligent being making any other move.} 
