8. Qxe6 {Now, White will not get his pawn back, so he should be energetic.} 
9. b3
9. cxb3
10. axb3 {With Bc1-b2 and Na3-c4 coming next, a huge lead in development, a healthy bishop pair, and a big pawn center, White's compensation is through the roof. It really surprises me that the machine claims he is only slightly better, but of course, that is still good enough for our purposes. I really would not want to play Black here.} 
