1. c4
1. Nf6 {1... Nf6 surely should be considered the more traditional move order if Black is aiming to play a King's Indian, but the positions we are covering here resemble the Grunfeld much more as Black is aiming to play d7-d5. Given that I don't think the plans involving Nf6xd5 are any good for him, I actually think 1... Nf6 is a poor move order when trying to execute this strategy.} 
