11. d5 {Now that e4 is sufficiently protected, Black is not able to make any trouble with Nd7-c5.} 
11. Qc7
12. Be3 {White has reached ideal coordination and can start gaining space on the queenside. Black's position is totally not set up to play any kind of King's Indian attack. His rook on e8 in particular is badly misplaced. Not only does it no longer support the f7-f5 break, but it also denies the e8-square from the f6-knight, which would be the best way to push f7-f5 through anyway.} 
