14. O-O
15. Re1
15. Re8
16. Bxe7
16. Rxe7
17. Nb4 {More piece exchanges are on the way. White is ready for some combination of Ra1-b1, Nf3-d2, and eventually b2-b3. Black's position looks uncomfortable to me, and it says a lot that the machine is recommending a very weird-looking move Re7-e6. I would strongly prefer White here.} 
