15. Rc2 {I think this is White's most testing try if Black does nothing. He wants Rd1-c1 and Qe2-d1 next. Then, he will be ready for Nf3-d4 to provoke Black into playing c7-c5. It is a slow and convoluted plan, but if Black is playing Re8, Bf8, and h6, why not? We aren't worried about counterplay.} 
