10. Nb8 {The machine's second choice is to bring the knight back to b8, offering a repetition and hoping to regroup the knight to c6. But this allows White to perfectly illustrate his idea.} 
11. Na3
11. Nc6
12. Bb2 {White is ready for Qd1-e2 and Na3-c2, and I don't believe Black will be able to maintain his pawn on d4. White looks pleasantly better.} 
