6. Qc2 {With the kingside knights already developed, we would bring the queen to b3 instead. But here, the position is a little different.} 
6. Bb7
7. a4 {Again, this move proves powerful.} 
7. a6
8. Nh3 {I like this unusual-looking development scheme. The knight on h3 makes a lot of sense once Black has committed to taking on c4, since now the open g2-a8 diagonal means Black will have a lot of trouble pushing c6-c5 through. White has an easy plan for the rest of his pieces, and should be pleasantly better.} 
