12. Bb7
13. Nxd7
13. Nxd7
14. d5 {White has a fantastic position with his space in the center and can look to follow up with Rf1-d1 and e2-e4 next. Black can never take on d5 without losing his bishop pair, and he just looks miserable to me.} 
