6. Bxd5 {Now, White has more than one good move, but I like an especially savage one.} 
7. Nc3 {Surprisingly, White can completely ignore a massive threat here and continue along with normal development as if nothing happened. He has an easy plan with e2-e4 coming next. Should Black take the rook in the corner, his position is immediately resignable after Qd1-b3.7.f3White is surely better here as well, but I like going for maximum punishment.} 
7. Bxh1 {7...Nf6This should be preferred, but after the natural8.f3with e2-e4 to follow, Black's position remains miserable.} 
8. Qb3 {Despite the rook up, Black is crushed.} 
