5. Qb3 {Black faces immediate and concrete problems. In general, this is a big appeal of choosing the English move order as opposed to the Reti- the inclusion of c2-c4 and c7-c6 makes it harder for Black to get the bishop outside of the pawn chain and push e7-e6 before Qd1-b3 becomes an issue.} 
5. Qb6 {5...Qc76.d4!⩲White is ready for Bc1-f4 next, and he has a fantastic version of a normal Slav. Any Slav player knows that when in doubt, you meet Qd1-b3 with Qd8-b6, not Qd8-c7.} 
