9. O-O {Now, White has a very basic plan. control the e4 square, push e2-e4, and then push d4 as well, pointing out that after cxd4 Nxd4, Black will not be able to exchange on g2 and the bishop on c6 will be vulnerable.} 
9. Nbd7 {With this move, Black is making the case that he might be able to push e7-e5, taking more space in the center.} 
