11. Bxg2 {And now a final powerful move seals Black's fate.11...Be712.Bxc6bxc613.Nf3±One look at Black's queenside structure is enough to know who should be better.} 
12. Qb3 {Black is forced to put his queen on e7, which completely uncoordinates his pieces and has him falling even further behind in development. He should be basically lost. It is not too surprising that he cannot survive the position opening when in his first 11 moves, he has played Bc8-g6-e6-d5-c6-g2. This is a lot of wasted time.} 
