13. a6 {This was seen in one of the human encounters. White chose d2-d4, which is good, but he has something even stronger.} 
14. d3 {Paying no heed to material, White tears open the position at all costs. The computer claims he is already winning, but I dug a bit deeper since we are going down another piece after Black takes on b5.} 
14. axb5
15. Be3
15. Qc8
16. axb5 {White is ready to take c4, push his queenside pawns, and abuse the b-file.} 
16. Nd5
17. dxc4
17. Nxe3
18. Qd2+
18. Ke8
19. Qxe3 {White is ready for Ra1-a7 and b7-b6. He is totally crushing on the queenside while 8 points worth of material are stuck and unable to fight back.} 
