16. Qxa4
16. Bxa4
17. b3
17. cxb3
18. axb3
18. Bxb3
19. Rf1 {White will win the a7-pawn and keep some initiative thanks to his more active pieces. At very high depths, the computer claims this should be equal, and I have to believe that if he makes it here, his chances of holding the endgame should be quite high. Still, making it here is not easy, it requires knowing this Bd7 move, and meeting the until now unknown Rf1-d1 with very accurate play, and even then, the draw is not gauranteed.} 
